    "description": "An exciting career opportunity awaits you at LV Prasad Eye Institute. We are on the lookout for a dedicated Consultant Physician to strengthen our Jabalpur-based team.\n\nAbout LV Prasad Eye Institute:\nLV Prasad Eye Institute is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n• Conduct routine health assessments and screenings\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n• Respond to medical emergencies and provide immediate care\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Arch / M.Arch from recognized institution\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in Telemedicine\n• Proficiency in ICU Management\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in CPT Codes\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Referral bonus program\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Learning & development budget\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Jabalpur, Madhya Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with LV Prasad Eye Institute!",
